    /**
     * Checks whether wrapping should be avoided after an elvis operator.
     *
     * When the right-hand side of an elvis operator is already on a new line, wrapping after the operator
     * would cause the line to end with the elvis operator. This creates an endless loop because:
     * 1. BinaryExpressionWrappingRule wraps after the elvis operator
     * 2. ChainWrappingRule detects the line ending with elvis operator and moves it to the next line
     * 3. This causes the line to exceed max_line_length again
     * 4. BinaryExpressionWrappingRule wraps again
     * 5. Endless loop
